# The rolling agent digest — THE SOURCE (F80 / kb:async-digest).
#
# Findings live HERE, as graph entities. reckons-workspace/DIGEST.md is GENERATED from
# this file and must never be hand-edited — 'npm run align' fails if it drifts.
#
# The digest is where we record our own failures. A record of honesty kept as a second
# source of truth, in a product whose thesis is that there should not be one, was a
# hypocrisy worth fixing.
#
# Append with: npx tsx scripts/agent/digest.ts --type bug-found --headline "…"

@prefix kpred: <urn:kbase:predicate/>.
@prefix ktype: <urn:kbase:type/>.
@prefix f: <urn:reckons:finding/>.

f:fvwv2cg a ktype:Finding;
    kpred:finding-type "claim-falsified";
    kpred:headline "The '60-70% token reduction' claim was false — measured ~18%";
    kpred:found-at "2026-07-13T02:23:34.835Z";
    kpred:about "kb:context-compression";
    kpred:detail "First test ever written for kb_compress falsified its headline claim. The format saves ~18% vs grouped Turtle (what a real .ttl looks like), ~29% vs flat. The 60-70% figure conflated the ENCODING with SUBGRAPH SELECTION, which is where the real saving lives. Corrected in the roadmap, the architecture graph, and the PUBLISHED docs.";
    kpred:agent "claude-code".
f:f1ei884p a ktype:Finding;
    kpred:finding-type "bug-found";
    kpred:headline "Confirming a fact made its source LESS trusted";
    kpred:found-at "2026-07-13T02:23:36.526Z";
    kpred:about "kb:trust-system";
    kpred:detail "getTrustScore discarded the baseline the moment any event existed. A trusted source collapsed 0.8 -> 0.05 on its first confirmation; 16 confirmations to recover. Using the review workflow correctly degraded your trust scores. Fixed: score = baseline + sum(delta * decay).";
    kpred:agent "claude-code".
f:fzoucrd a ktype:Finding;
    kpred:finding-type "bug-found";
    kpred:headline "Citations were never verified — a fabricated quote shipped as provenance";
    kpred:found-at "2026-07-13T02:23:38.292Z";
    kpred:about "kb:passage-grounding";
    kpred:detail "The prompt says 'copy it exactly, do not paraphrase'. Nothing ever checked. triplesToStatements did not even RECEIVE the source text, so it structurally could not. Small models paraphrase constantly. For an app selling provenance, the user checks the receipt, it looks right, and it is a forgery. Now verified; a forged excerpt is DROPPED, not shown.";
    kpred:agent "claude-code".
