    kpred:detail "last_fired_at 2026-07-12T20:40:18Z, exactly on schedule. Zero commits, no error surfaced. Afterwards next_run_at still displayed a future time while enabled was false, so it LOOKED armed while being dead. A scheduler you cannot observe is not a scheduler. This is why orchestration comes home (F81).";
    kpred:agent "claude-code".
f:fzeejji a ktype:Finding;
    kpred:finding-type "bug-found";
    kpred:headline "PWA manifest locks orientation to portrait — on a graph app";
    kpred:found-at "2026-07-13T02:34:21.054Z";
    kpred:about "kb:mobile-ui";
    kpred:detail "vite.config.ts sets orientation:'portrait'. On a tablet this ruins the force-directed graph, which is the core surface. Raised as a question rather than changed unilaterally; it may be deliberate for phone onboarding.";
    kpred:agent "claude-code".
f:fz4lkfp a ktype:Finding;
    kpred:finding-type "note";
    kpred:headline "Correction: the cron did not fail — the runner and the reporting did";
    kpred:found-at "2026-07-13T02:35:54.509Z";
    kpred:about "kb:local-orchestration";
    kpred:detail "The cron fired at exactly 20:40:18Z as scheduled. The cloud AGENT produced no commits, and nothing surfaced that. Calling it 'the cron failed' would send us to fix the wrong component. Design conclusion: the QUEUE is the contract and the RUNNER is pluggable — in-app Web Worker for reach (every device), an optional desktop process driven by cron/launchd/Task Scheduler for wake-when-closed, MCP server when an agent is already connected. No single runner is load-bearing, so none can silently stop the system.";
    kpred:agent "claude-code".
f:fpjdyho a ktype:Finding;
    kpred:finding-type "bug-found";
    kpred:headline "The graph view drew literals as nodes — 1234 nodes for a 233-entity graph";
    kpred:found-at "2026-07-13T02:51:48.077Z";
    kpred:about "kb:graph-legibility";
    kpred:detail "Not a perf problem: a modelling mistake in the view. 96% of distinct literal values in the roadmap appear exactly ONCE — leaves that connect nothing. A literal earns a node by being SHARED. Fixed: 1234 nodes -> 271 (78% fewer); 985 walls of text moved to the node panel.";
    kpred:agent "claude-code".
f:fy8x78g a ktype:Finding;
    kpred:finding-type "decision-needed";
    kpred:headline "TriG: what does the 4th element MEAN? (source vs KB — it cannot be both)";
    kpred:found-at "2026-07-13T02:55:37.538Z";
    kpred:about "kb:rdf-dataset-migration";
    kpred:detail "Measured: 18 of 19 repo .ttl files declare 0-1 sources, so a named graph carries ZERO information for them — they stay .ttl forever. TriG earns its place at EXPORT: toTurtle() currently DROPS g, so after ingesting 5 PDFs and exporting, 'where did this fact come from?' is unanswerable. Its prov block is orphaned decoration. That is the real bug TriG fixes.";
    kpred:agent "claude-code".
f:fqrih5o a ktype:Finding;
    kpred:finding-type "decision-needed";
    kpred:headline "TTL/TriG is not a format choice — it is two products";
    kpred:found-at "2026-07-13T03:16:07.647Z";
    kpred:about "kb:ttl-trig-split";
    kpred:detail "PROVENANCE IS AN ACCOUNTABILITY RELATION, NOT A FIELD. A source the user controls and can rewrite is self-attestation, not evidence — 'the user is a failure and a fool at times' is a THREAT MODEL, not an insult. A private graph therefore has NO provenance and needs none: it makes no claim on anybody. Publishing is the moment a graph acquires an OWNER and therefore acquires provenance — official publication, not manual file-sharing, which transfers no accountability. TTL = private, offline, full user power. TriG = published, attributed, governed; RBAC + 3Ps overlay (F84). Separate market, separate marketing angle. NOTE: this is the third time the same principle has surfaced — an unverifiable claim, made by the party it benefits, is not evidence (cf. F66.1 attestation, F82 forced links).";
    kpred:agent "claude-code".
f:f1bmvd1l a ktype:Finding;
    kpred:finding-type "shipped";
    kpred:headline "The thesis is on the landing page — generated from the graph, not hand-written";
